		<p>Dear Stanislav,</p>
<p>On what basis do you claim (or at least imply) that the combination of a typical OS kernel&#8217;s memory allocator and a dynamic language runtime&#8217;s garbage collector has any perceptible impact on responsiveness? I&#8217;m genuinely curious.</p>
<p>Thanks,<br />
Matt</p>

