<p>Given that a 4GHz machine can be less responsive than a 1980&#8217;s minicomputer (or even a 1980&#8217;s DOS machine), on what factual basis do you claim that the problem is between the kernel&#8217;s memory allocator and the runtime&#8217;s garbage collector?</p>

		<div class="reply">
		<a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='/?p=300&#038;cpage=1&#038;replytocom=16421#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("div-comment-16421", "16421", "respond", "300")'>Reply</a>		</div>
