		<li class="comment byuser comment-author-stas bypostauthor even depth-6" id="comment-16423">
				<div id="div-comment-16423" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<cite class="fn"><a href='http://www.loper-os.org' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Stanislav</a></cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>

		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://www.loper-os.org/?p=300&amp;cpage=1#comment-16423">May 14, 2014 at 3:17 pm</a></div>

		<p>Dear Mike Stimpson,</p>
<p>Of course, this is by far not the <i>only</i> issue at work here.  To understand what was meant, consider the concept of impedance mismatch &#8211; as applied to cases such as the expansion of a road causing an <i>increase</i> in traffic jams &#8211; or, more appropriately to our discussion &#8211; <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/B%C3%A9l%C3%A1dy's_anomaly" rel="nofollow">Bélády&#8217;s anomaly</a> and related phenomena.</p>
<p>You <i>really</i> don&#8217;t want memory allocators (esp. with GC) operating on top of one another. Feel free to verify this experimentally.</p>
<p>Yours,<br />
-Stanislav</p>

